cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SI 

The paper presents a new model for Gaussian process latent variable modeling that can handle data with attributes of different types. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on modeling and inference, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
